member.summary:
Gets or sets the  javascript function to call before the context menu is shown for the row.
The javascript code can be formatted like: function BeforeShowContextMenuForRow(metafuseTable, contextMenu, localEvent, rowId){return true;};
Return true to continue to show the menu, return false to not show the menu.

members.member:
The PropertyDefinitionDataSet object handles the business logic and data access for the specialized business object, PropertyDefinitionDataSet. The class inherits from class. G
See the examples of how to construct the PropertyDefinitionDataSet object.
To create a new instance of a new of PropertyDefinitionDataSet. PropertyDefinitionDataSet o = (PropertyDefinitionDataSet)this.Registry.CreateInstance(typeof(PropertyDefinitionDataSet));
To create an new instance of an existing PropertyDefinitionDataSet. PropertyDefinitionDataSet o = (PropertyDefinitionDataSet)this.Registry.CreateInstance(typeof(PropertyDefinitionDataSet), new Guid("{250426B4-3C7A-463c-93C4-045668C8A1AA}"));
In order to create an instance of PropertyDefinitionDataSet, you need to have a object created, and have set the static member to the and objects.

example.code:
using(SqlDataReaderWrapper dr = new SqlDataReaderWrapper("server=(local); database=Northwind; trusted_connection=true"))
{
	dr.ProcedureName = "MyProcedureName";
	dr.AddString("StringParameter", "test value");
	dr.Execute();

	Response.Write(dr.GetStringValue("OutputString"));
}

//OR equivalently

SqlDataReaderWrapper dr = new SqlDataReaderWrapper("server=(local); database=Northwind; trusted_connection=true")

try
{
	dr.ProcedureName = "MyProcedureName";
	dr.AddString("StringParameter", "test value");
	dr.Execute();

	Response.Write(dr.GetStringValue("OutputString"));
}
finally
{
	if(dr != null)
	{
		dr.Dispose();
	}
}

